    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is showing a BSOD (Blue Screen of Death) with the stop code `WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR`. They've had this at least a couple times yesterday. They want me to:\n\n1. Investigate using proper enterprise root cause analysis\n2. Tell them its fixability score using iFix (I think they mean iFixit or a similar tool/score)\n3. Tell them how reliable it is\n4. Whether they can improve their PC temperature\n5. All components are okay but they don't want to stress test them\n6. They want a decent assessment using PowerShell or Python tools and ensure those work\n\nLet me break this down:\n\n1. **Root Cause Analysis for WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR**: This is a hardware-related error. WHEA stands for Windows Hardware Error Architecture. Common causes include:\n   - CPU issues (overclocking, overheating, voltage issues)\n   - RAM problems\n   - Motherboard issues\n   - Power supply issues\n   - Driver conflicts\n\n2. **Fixability Score**: I'll need to explain what iFixit repairability scores mean and how they might apply to PC components. However, iFixit scores are typically for physical devices (phones, laptops, etc.), not software/BSOD errors. I should clarify this.\n\n3. **Temperature monitoring**: They want to check PC temperatures without stress testing.\n\n4. **PowerShell/Python tools**: They want me to provide actual tools they can use.\n\nLet me start by creating a todo list and then providing the analysis and tools.\n\nFirst, let me check what tools are available on the system. I'll check for common diagnostic tools and then create PowerShell/Python scripts they can use.",
      "timestamp": 1783146204551
    },
