    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Excellent - I now have critical evidence. Let me analyze what I found:\n\n1. **HP laptop** with Intel i5-7300HQ (Kaby Lake) - this is an older CPU (2017 era)\n2. **XTU3SERVICE timeout** - Intel Extreme Tuning Utility service is failing to start. This is a MAJOR clue - XTU is used for overclocking/undervolting\n3. **Kernel-Power Event 41** - System rebooted without proper shutdown (BSOD crashes)\n4. **Event ID 6008** - Unexpected system shutdowns logged5. **volmgr Event 161** - Dump file creation FAILED - this is why the BSOD gets stuck at 0%\n6. **Firmware Version F.24** - HP BIOS\n7. **TPM-WMI errors** - Secure boot issues but not directly related to WHEA\n\nKey findings:\n- XTU3SERVICE timeout suggests Intel XTU is installed and possibly being used for CPU tuning/overclocking\n- i5-7300HQ is a laptop CPU (locked, not overclockable normally), but undervolting via XTU is possible\n- Failed dump file creation explains the stuck0% on BSOD\n- Multiple crashes on 03/07/2026\n\nLet me gather more info.",
      "timestamp": 1783146279900
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"Get-CimInstance Win32_BaseBoard | Select-Object Manufacturer, Product, SerialNumber, Version\", \"description\": \"Get motherboard details\"}",
