    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a complete picture:\n\n- **HP OMEN Laptop 15-ce0xx** - Gaming laptop\n- **Intel i5-7300HQ** (2.5GHz, Kaby Lake)\n- **NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1050** + Intel HD 630\n- **16GB RAM** (~17053446144 bytes)\n- **BIOS F.24**\n- **XTU3SERVICE** is installed and timing out\n\nThis is a gaming laptop. The WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR on this hardware with XTU installed strongly suggests CPU undervolting instability.\n\nLet me check for more details about temperatures and XTU settings.",
      "timestamp": 1783146308191
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"Get-Service -Name \\\"*XTU*\\\",\\\"*Intel*Overclock*\\\",\\\"*Intel*Extreme*\\\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, Status, StartType\", \"description\": \"Check Intel XTU service status\"}",
      "output": "\r\nName         Status StartType\r\n----         ------ ---------\r\nXTU3SERVICE Stopped Automatic\r\n\r\n\r\n",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783146323093
