      "text": "Now I have enough data to provide a comprehensive analysis. Let me create the diagnostic PowerShell tools and provide the assessment.\n\nKey findings:\n1. HP OMEN Laptop 15-ce0xx\n2. Intel i5-7300HQ (locked, not overclockable)\n3. NVIDIA GTX 1050\n4. 16GB RAM\n5. BIOS F.24\n6. Intel XTU service installed but failing (XTU3SERVICE timeout)\n7. Two crashes on 03/07/2026 at ~10:14 and ~16:14\n8. Both times: Kernel-Power Event 41 + volmgr Event 161 (dump creation failed)\n9. CrashDumpEnabled = 7 (full kernel dump enabled)\n10. But dump files are not being created successfullyThe XTU service being installed and failing is suspicious. The i5-7300HQ is not overclockable, but XTU can be used for undervolting. If undervolting is unstable, it would cause WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR.\n\nLet me now create the diagnostic tools and provide the full assessment.",
