      "output": "Title: HP OMEN Series Repair Help: Learn How to Fix It Yourself.\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/Device/HP_Omen\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nFind free step-by-step repair instructions, manuals, schematics, community support, and other DIY resources. Repair Repair information for the HP OMEN laptop ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement - iFixit Repair Guide\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/HP+Omen+15-CE0XX+Fan+Replacement/157629\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nHP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement - iFixit Repair Guide\n...\n# HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement\n...\nThis guide will walk you through the process of replacing a faulty ventilation fan in your HP Omen 15-CE0XX laptop. A malfunctioning fan can cause overheating and system instability, leading to potential permanent damage to your device. It is important to take appropriate precautions before beginning the fan replacement process to ensure a successful outcome.\n...\nBefore starting, make sure to power down your laptop completely and disconnect from any external power source. It is recommended to back up your data and review any troubleshooting steps to ensure that the fan is indeed the root cause of the issue.\n...\nThroughout the process, you will need basic tools such as screwdrivers, prying tools and a replacement fan that is compatible with the HP Omen 15-CE0XX. You should follow the instructions closely and handle the internal components with care to avoid any damage.\n...\nOnce you have completed the fan replacement, it is important to test your laptop to ensure that it is running correctly and without overheating. This guide is intended for individuals with basic technical skills, but if you are unsure or not confident in your abilities, it is always best to seek professional assistance\n...\nUse a plastic opening tool to gently separate the bottom cover from the main chassis,\n...\npull the cover\n...\nUnscrew the four 5.5 mm screws that connect the battery to the main system, and gently detach the battery.\n...\nRemove the trunk outlet for the replacement fan. This is done by unscrewing the three 5.5mm screws on the trunk outlet and then sliding it outwards to remove.\n...\nUse a Phillips #00 screwdriver to unscrew the five 5.5 mm screws that secure the bracket to the frame.\n...\n## Step\n...\nDisconnect the fan cable from the motherboard using a plastic opening/ pry tool.\n...\nDo not use too much force while pulling the fan cable as it may break. If required, you may use a secondary plastic opening/pry tool for support.\n...\n## Step 7\n...\nCarefully pull the fan out, clean the dust if required.\n...\nFinally, you can now replace the faulty fan with the new fan by following the above steps in reverse order.\n...\nTo reassemble your device, follow these instructions in reverse order.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Laptop Repairability Scores | Most Repairable Laptops - iFixit\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/laptop-repairability-scores\nPublished: 2026-06-29T03:09:35.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nOur engineers tear down the latest laptops and score their repairability from 0 to 10. What are the most repairable laptops? Let's find out.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Repairability - iFixit\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/repairability\nPublished: 2026-06-29T03:10:30.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nRepairability means making it possible—and ideally easy—to repair a product. A repairable product is designed with disassembly in mind.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Solved: battery replacement for omen 15 ce001nj - HP Support Community - 9548356\nURL: https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Notebook-Hardware-and-Upgrade-Questions/battery-replacement-for-omen-15-ce001nj/td-p/9548356\nPublished: 2025-12-01T10:28:59.000Z\nAuthor: Author\nHighlights:\nBelow is the link to the service manual:\n...\nOMEN by HP 15 Notebook PC (model numbers 15-ce000 through 15-ce099) Maintenance and Service Guide\n...\nChapter 3, page 22 has the battery part number and description.\n...\nBattery (4-cell, 70-WHr, 4.55-AH, Li-ion) HP part # 917724-855\n...\nChapters 4 and 5 have the battery removal and replacement procedures.\n...\nBelow is the link to the service manual:\n...\nOMEN by HP 15 Notebook PC (model numbers 15-ce000 through 15-ce099) Maintenance and Service Guide\n...\nChapter 3, page 22 has the battery part number and description.\n...\nBattery (4-cell, 70-WHr, 4.55-AH, Li-ion) HP part # 917724-855\n...\nChapters 4 and 5 have the battery removal and replacement procedures.\n\n---\n\nTitle: HP Omen 15 (15-ce000, ce100) - Specs, Tests, and Prices | LaptopMedia UK\nURL: https://laptopmedia.com/gb/series/hp-omen-15-15-ce000/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nHP Omen 15 (15-ce000, ce100) - Specs, Tests, and Prices | LaptopMedia UK\n...\n#### HP Omen 15 (15-ce000, ce100) - Specs\n...\nHP Omen\n...\n## HP Omen 15 (15\n...\n## Buy our profiles for AUO B156HAN04.4 / 15.6”, Full HD (1920 x 1080), IPS\n...\nedd_item edd_id_1='82159' edd_id_2='82162' edd_id_3='82165' edd_id_4='82167']\n...\n## CPU performance\n...\nHere you can find the price/performance difference between all the CPUs that come in the HP Omen 15 (15-ce000, ce100) series.\n...\n## Results are from the Cinebench 20 Multi-core test (the higher the score, the better)\n...\n## GPU performance\n...\nHere you can find the price/performance difference between all the GPUs that come in the HP Omen 15 (15-ce000, ce100) series.\n...\n## The results are from 3DMark Time Spy (Graphics). Higher is better.\n\n---\n\nTitle: iFixit and HP Expand Partnership, Making More Laptops Repairable Than Ever\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/News/109015/ifixit-and-hp-expand-partnership\nPublished: 2026-07-03T20:03:16.000Z\nAuthor: Matt Zieminski\nHighlights:\niFixit and HP are teaming up to provide full repair support for seven EliteBook models and launch the brand-new Revivekit battery ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: Upgrade review of HP OMEN by Laptop 15-ce... #0b3e581bae\nURL: https://linux-hardware.org/?probe=0b3e581bae&upgrade=\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: Andrey Ponomarenko\nHighlights:\nUpgrade review of HP OMEN by Laptop 15-ce... #0b3e581bae\n...\n## Probe #0b3e581bae (Upgrade Review) of HP OMEN by Laptop 15-ce...\n...\nThis is an upgrade review of original probe.\n...\n| System | Ubuntu 20.04 |\n| --- | --- |\n| Arch | x86_64 |\n| Kernel | 5.4.0-52-generic |\n| Vendor | Hewlett-Packard» |\n| Model | OMEN by Laptop 15-ce0xx» |\n| Year | 2017 |\n| HWid | A5B54» |\n| Type | notebook |\n| DE | GNOME (X11) |\n...\n## Devices (43) + Upgrade options (275)\n...\nhp-primary-li-ion-62-\n...\n62",
