      "output": "Title: Ultimate Guide to Laptop Cooling Pads for HP Gaming Laptops (2025)\nURL: https://www.hp.com/us-en/shop/tech-takes/best-laptop-cooling-pads\nPublished: 2025-01-31T08:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nBest Cooling Pads for HP Laptops in 2025\n___HP Victus 15 Cooling Pad: Look for cooling pads with multiple fans that align with the laptop's intake vents. ...\n___HP Omen Cooling Pad: Gaming-focused cooling pads with RGB lighting complement the Omen's aesthetic while providing necessary cooling. highlights: [Best Cooling Pads for HP Laptops in 2025]\n\n---\n\nTitle: Cooling Pad for HP Omen 17 16 15 15t Transcend 14 16 MAX 16 Victus 15 16 Pavilion 14-17 inch Gaming Laptop,with Ultra Powerful Booster Turbo Fan,6 RGB Light Mode,Adjustable Speed,Touch Start - Newegg.com\nURL: https://www.newegg.com/p/3C6-012R-007M3\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nCooling Pad for HP Omen 17 16 15 15t Transcend 14 16 MAX 16 Victus 15 16 Pavilion 14-17 inch Gaming Laptop,with Ultra Powerful Booster Turbo Fan,6 RGB Light Mode,Adjustable Speed,Touch Start - Newegg.com\n...\n# Cooling Pad for HP Omen 17 16 15 15t Transcend 14 16 MAX 16 Victus 15 16 Pavilion 14-17 inch Gaming Laptop,with Ultra Powerful Booster Turbo Fan,6 RGB Light Mode,Adjustable Speed,Touch Start\n...\n- A good product can only be known by experiencing it yourself. This cooling pad, which can be called a heat dissipation monster, is designed specifically for gaming laptops and can fully reach the level you want, even higher. Its appearance is cool and high-end, and it is obvious that it is not a cheap item and worth owning. Rapid Heat Dissipation--Super Powerful Turbofan(800-3500 RPM) with Sealed Wind Pressure Reduces CPU+GPU Temperature By 40 Degrees in 90 Seconds(Different Laptop May Have Different Cooling Effects). Quickly Solve Laptop Heating Problems, Improve Laptop Performance, and Make Laptop Work More Smoothly.\n...\n- Multiple Patented Designs--Retractable Side Panels Prevent The Laptop From Slipping. Foldable Footrests Supports Compatibility with Laptops of Different Sizes Ranging From 15 to 18 inches , Gaming Laptop, Office Laptop etc.\n...\n- USB HUB--Built-in 1 Type-C Data Input Port 3 USB HUB Data Transmission Port, Can Connect External Devices Such As Keyboards, Mouse, a\n...\nCooling Pad for HP Omen 17 16 15 15t Transcend 14 16 MAX 16 Victus 15 16 Pavilion 14-17 inch Gaming Laptop, with Ultra Powerful Booster Turbo Fan, 6 RGB Light Mode, Adjustable Speed, Touch Start\n...\n| Additional Information | First Listed on Newegg | June 07, 2026 |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n\n---\n\nTitle: Best Laptop Cooling Pads for Gaming Right Now: Our Tested Picks\nURL: https://www.ign.com/articles/best-laptop-cooling-pad\nPublished: 2025-04-16T16:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: By  Chris Coke Updated :  Jan 30, 2026 9:37pm UTC 84 comments\nHighlights:\nThe Best Laptop Cooling Pads Right Now: These Coolers Actually Work · 1. Razer Laptop Cooling Pad · 2. Havit HV-F2701 · 3. IETS GT600 V2 Laptop ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: Best Cooling Pad for HP Omen 16 - Accessories Tested\nURL: https://www.accessorytested.com/best-cooling-pad-for-hp-omen-16/\nPublished: 2026-05-04T18:53:35.000Z\nAuthor: admin\nHighlights:\n12 cooling pads based on\n...\nthree-hour gaming loops in a controlled 72°F environment, measuring CPU/GPU deltas with the Omen Hub software. I specifically looked for pads that aligned with the Omen’s unique rearward bottom intake vents and tested the structural integrity of the risers under the weight of this 5.3lb laptop.\n...\nThe KLIM Ultimate is the sweet spot for Omen 16 owners who want a significant upgrade over cheap generic pads without the “wind tunnel” noise of the IETS. It features a massive 200mm fan that covers nearly the entire underside of the laptop. In my testing, this provided a very consistent airflow that lowered\n...\ntemps by about 5-7°C. While it doesn’t have the pressure-seal of our top pick, the metal mesh surface dissipates heat extremely well, and the fan is remarkably quiet even at full speed. I find the RGB ring around the edge adds a nice touch of flair that matches the Omen’s aesthetic perfectly.\n...\nIf you’ve already stretched your budget to buy the Omen 16 and just need something reliable to keep it off the desk surface, the Havit HV-F2056 is the gold standard for budget cooling. It uses three 110mm fans that spin at a respectable 1100 RPM. In my hands-on testing, I noticed that the three-fan layout aligns surprisingly well with the Omen 16’s intake vents, providing a modest but helpful 3-4°C drop. It’s incredibly slim and lightweight, making it the best choice for students or professionals who carry their Omen in a backpack.\n...\nWhen shopping for a cooling pad for your HP Omen 16, the most important factor is understanding your laptop’s airflow. The Omen 16 pulls air from the bottom and exhausts it out the back and sides. A pad that just blows air weakly against the plastic shell won’t help much. You need either high-pressure airflow (like the IETS) or fans that align perfectly with the intake grilles (like the Cooler Master). Prioritize models with adjustable heights to improve ergonomics, as the Omen 16 is quite a heavy machine and proper positioning can prevent wrist fatigue during long sessions.\n...\nNoise Tolerance: High\n...\nChoosing the right cooling pad depends entirely on how you use your Omen 16. If you are a hardcore gamer who plays demanding titles at max settings, the IETS GT500 is the only choice that offers “desktop-level” thermal stability. If you need a versatile stand for a mix of office work and moderate gaming, the KLIM Ultimate provides the best user experience without the noise. For students on the move, the Havit is a no-brainer for its portability. As laptop components get more powerful every year, a high-quality cooling pad is no longer just an accessory—it’s a necessary insurance policy for your hardware’s longevity.\n\n---\n\nTitle: The best laptop cooling pads of 2026: Expert tested | ZDNET\nURL: https://www.zdnet.com/home-and-office/best-laptop-cooling-pad/\nPublished: 2026-06-10T09:00:55.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nWhy we like it: I found the Llano V12 Laptop Cooling Pad to be the best overall option for multiple reasons. It is well-designed with a recessed ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: Best Laptop Cooling Pads for Gaming in 2026\nURL: https://baseoftech.com/best-laptop-cooling-pads-for-gaming/\nPublished: 2026-02-11T23:43:18.000Z\nAuthor: Fares\nHighlights:\nRazer Laptop Cooling Pad (Best overall gaming pad) · IETS GT600 V2 RGB (Best for overheating gaming laptops) · Llano V12-style sealed cooler (Best ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: HP HyperX OMEN 15 (2026) Review: A machine built for long-session stability - The Hindu\nURL: https://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/technology/gadgets/hp-hyperx-omen-15-2026-review-a-machine-built-for-long-session-stability/article70941649.ece\nPublished: 2026-05-05T06:35:16.000Z\nAuthor: Haider Ali Khan\nHighlights:\n# HP HyperX OMEN 15 (2026) Review | A machine built for long-session stability\n...\nHP’s attempt to refine that balance by transforming high-\n...\nan unusually responsive\n...\n50-series\n...\nperformance-focused\n...\n2.42kg,\n...\nperformance-class category\n...\nthan the portability segment.\n...\nchassis measures 34.3 × 25.3 × 2.25 cm, making\n...\nheavier than creator-focused alternatives. Build quality\n...\nthough the lid still shows a small amount of flex under pressure. The hinge remains\n...\nand gaming sessions,\n...\nenlarged venting areas\n...\nslimness.\n...\nPort selection is practical and gaming-ready. The laptop includes two USB-A ports, one USB-C port with DisplayPort 1.4 and power delivery support, HDMI 2.1, an RJ-45 Ethernet port, and a headphone combo jack. However, the USB-C port is routed through the integrated graphics rather than directly through the NVIDIA GPU. This means some high-bandwidth VR headsets that require direct dGPU access may not function optimally. The reduced rear-port layout also improves airflow efficiency, aligning with the system’s hyperbaric cooling architecture.\n...\nThermal management remains one of the strongest aspects of this refresh. OMEN Tempest Cooling integrates dual side fans, enlarged rear vents, and additional bottom airflow channels to improve heat dissipation. Even after extended sessions of Warhammer 40,000: Space Marine 2, the palm rests remained comfortable, highlighting the effectiveness of the cooling layout. Fan noise becomes audible when the HX processor is pushed aggressively, but temperatures remain controlled throughout long gaming runs.\n...\nThe HP HyperX OMEN 15 (2026) focuses less on headline specifications and more on sustained gaming consistency. Its strengths lie in responsive input performance, effective thermal engineering, and a well-balanced 2.5K 180Hz display that suits both esports titles and modern AAA games. Features such as OMEN AI tuning and hyperbaric airflow design reinforce its position as a machine built for long-session stability rather than short benchmark bursts.\n...\nWhile similarly priced alternatives like Lenovo’s LOQ series or the Asus V16 can deliver comparable GPU performance at lower cost, the OMEN differentiates itself through stronger thermal management and a more refined high-refresh display experience. Native 4K gaming remains outside its comfort zone, and the USB-C routing limitation may affect some VR users. However, for competitive players and creators looking for a reliable hybrid workstation capable of strong 1080p and 2.5K performance, the HyperX OMEN 15 remains a compelling choice in its segment.\n\n---\n\nTitle: HYPERX OMEN 15 AMD GAMING LAPTOP| HP® Official Site\nURL: https://www.hp.com/us-en/gaming-pc/laptops/2026-omen-15-amd.html\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe HyperX OMEN 15 goes beyond what you’d expect from a 15-inch gaming laptop. Built to hold up when you’re hopping on for a quick game or as it starts to get competitive. OMEN 15 brings solid performance with fast, responsive inputs, with our OMEN Tempest Cooling architecture running in the background so nothing slows you down. The only thing you have to think about is your next move.​\n...\nOMEN TEMPEST COOLING​\n...\nHeat buildup can slow things down, but OMEN Tempest Cooling is built to keep performance consistent by improving airflow at every level. With ports kept at the rear for more ventilation and additional vents that help push out more heat efficiently, this laptop handles longer gaming sessions without slowing you down. And with our self-cleaning fan technology, Fan Cleaner, your fans will automatically change direction between gaming sessions—never during—and expel any accumulated dust. You can also go into OGH and manually run it or adjust the schedule yourself.​",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783147110418
