      "output": "Title: HWiNFO® Licenses - HWiNFO\nURL: https://www.hwinfo.com/licenses/\nPublished: 2023-07-25T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nHWiNFO® tools are available in various versions for different systems and use cases.All versions are free to use in personal and non-commercial environments.Using HWiNFO® 64 or HWiNFO® ARM64 in a commercial environment requires the HWiNFO® 64/ARM64 Pro license. The Pro license also offers additional features.\n...\n| HWiNFO® 64HWiNFO® ARM64 | HWiNFO® 64 ProHWiNFO® ARM64 Pro | HWiNFO® 32 | HWiNFO® for DOS |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Operating system | Windows 7 and later (64-bit) | Windows 7 and later (64-bit) | Windows 95 and later (32/64-bit)1 | MS-DOS or compatible |\n| Non-Commercial use |\n| Commercial use | 2 | 3 |\n| Automatic report via command-line |\n| Automatic sensor logging via command-line |\n| Automatic Update |\n| Shared Memory Support | 12-hour limit4 | Unlimited | Unlimited |\n| OSD Maximum Items | 5 | Unlimited |\n| Remote Monitoring (max machines) | (5) 12-hour limit | (5 + n)5 |\n...\n3 HWiNFO® 64 Pro or HWiNFO® ARM64 Pro can be used in commercial environment only with the Engineer or Corporate License. The Personal license does not allow commercial use.\n...\n15 connections\n...\n300\n...\nSensor Monitoring in non-\n...\nHWiNFO® 64/ARM64 Pro is available with different types of licenses:\n...\n| Personal | Engineer | Corporate |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Commercial use |\n| License seal | 1 user, 5 computers | User-based | Computer-based |\n| Use in domain |\n| Volume discount |\n...\nAny Pro version purchased and covered by maintenance period is licensed perpetually (doesn't expire). Licenses available differ in the duration of maintenance period:\n...\n| Subscription | Lifetime |\n| --- | --- |\n| Maintenance period (updates covered) | 1, 2, 3 years | Perpetual |\n| Renewal discount | 50% - 60% | - |\n| Educational discount | 50% |\n| Initial price (1st year) from | $ 29 | $ 199 |\n| Renewal price (next year) from | $ 14.5 | - |\n| Purchase license | Buy Now | Buy Now |\n...\nA Subscription license is issued with a limited maintenance period during which the licensed subject is entitled to use the license key on all updates of the HWiNFO® 64/ARM64 Pro at no additional cost. After expiry of the maintenance period, versions issued before the expiry date will continue to work as licensed copies perpetually, but all versions released after that date will require a new license. A previously purchased license can be extended via a renewal request with a 50% discount. Existing customers can opt-in for auto-renew (automatic notification and renew when license is about to expire) or manual renew until cancelled. Renewal is optional and can be cancelled anytime.\n...\nA Lifetime License is a one-time purchase covering all future updates of HWiNFO® 64/ARM64 Pro.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Versions History | HWiNFO\nURL: https://www.hwinfo.com/version-history/\nPublished: 2018-09-21T15:05:45.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nof HWiNFO® 32/64\n...\nLatest v8.48\n...\nReleased on May-26-2026\n...\n- Fixed Corsair iCUE Link Hub support.\n- Improved support of next-generation AMD CPUs and APUs.\n- Added main report and sensor logging in JSON format [HWiNFO 64/ARM64 only].\n- Added main report and sensor logging in YAML format [HWiNFO 64/ARM64 only].\n- Added command-line option to add a note in report files.\n- Added monitoring of GC-HPWR (BTF connector) pin currents on ASUS BTF mainboards.\n...\n- Added KSC\n...\n.5 and 2.0 monitoring on Kontron systems.\n...\n- Improved support of soft-downcored AMD systems.\n...\n- Added limited support of Lisuan LX 7G100.\n...\n- Added fan speed monitoring on MSI\n...\n8.\n...\n- Improved Intel Nova Lake support.\n...\n- Enhanced sensor monitoring on\n...\nsun 2\n...\n5HX series.\n...\nLatest v8.48\n...\nReleased on May-26-2026\n...\n- Fixed Corsair iCUE Link Hub support.\n- Improved support of next-generation AMD CPUs and APUs.\n- Added main report and sensor logging in JSON format [HWiNFO 64/ARM64 only].\n...\n- Added main report and sensor logging in YAML format [HWiNFO 64/ARM64 only].\n...\n- Added command-line option to add a note in report files.\n...\n- Added monitoring of GC-HPWR (BTF connector) pin currents on ASUS BTF mainboards.\n...\n- Added KSC 1.5 and 2.0 monitoring on Kontron systems.\n...\n- Improved support of soft-downcored AMD systems.\n- Added limited support of Lisuan LX 7G100.\n...\nLatest v8.46\n...\nReleased on Apr-14-2026\n...\n- Enhanced sensor monitoring on ASRock X870\n...\n0E Challenger and X\n...\nichi OCF.\n...\nLatest v8.44\n...\nLatest v8.42\n...\nReleased on Feb-24\n...\n- Added monitoring\n...\nport on ASUS mainboards with\n...\n545x.\n...\n- Added dedicated NPU sensors for\n...\nNPUs.\n...\n- Added Thermal\n...\nView Pro II support.\n- Added NPU Stress Test (Pro only).\n...\nmonitoring on ASUS mainboards.\n...\nLatest v8.40\n...\nLatest v8.34\n...\nReleased on Nov-11-2025\n...\nLatest v8.32\n...\nReleased on Oct-14-2025\n...\n- Updated reporting\n...\n-S support.\n...\nminor updates and\n...\n- Enhanced sensor\n...\n- Added monitoring\n...\n- ARM64: Added preliminary support of\n...\nX2.\n...\n64: Added power monitoring for\n...\nLatest v8.30\n...\nReleased on Aug-\n...\n2-20\n...\nLatest v8.28\n...\nReleased on Jun-26-2025\n...\nmonitored (for\n...\n- Added OSD\n...\nLatest v8.26\n...\nLatest v8.24\n...\nLatest v8.22\n...\nReleased on Feb-26-2025\n...\nLatest v8.20\n...\nLatest v7.00\n...\nMar-09\n...\n2021\n...\n- HWiNFO64 is limited to non-commercial use only. Check License terms.\n- Introducing HWiNFO64 Pro for commercial use and additional features.\n...\n- Enhanced sensor monitoring on MSI H510 series mainboards.\n- Fixed monitoring of +12V on some ASUS Z590 series mainboards.\n...\n- Improved support of\n...\nPDDR3/LPDDR4/LPDDR4X memories.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Free Download HWiNFO Sofware | Installer & Portable for Windows, DOS\nURL: https://www.hwinfo.com/download/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n## Installerfor Windows 7 64-bit and laterx64 or ARM64 platform\n...\nVersion 8.48\n...\nAutomatic installer for HWiNFO® 64 or HWiNFO® ARM64 depending on platform.\n...\nHWiNFO® 64/ARM64 are FREEWARE for Non-Commercial use only. Check Licensing and upgrade to Pro.\n...\n## Portablefor Windows 95 and laterx86, x64 or ARM64 platform\n...\nVersion 8.48\n...\nDownload latest Beta v8.49-6005\n...\nPortable package containing HWiNFO® 32, HWiNFO® 64 and HWiNFO® ARM64. Also available as Beta pre-release versions.\n...\nHWiNFO® 32 (legacy) is FREEWARE.\n...\nHWiNFO® 64/ARM64 are FREEWARE for Non-Commercial use only. Check Licensing and upgrade to Pro.\n...\nHWiNFO® for DOS, useful for legacy systems running DOS. FREEWARE and free distributable as-is.\n\n---\n\nTitle: HWiNFO - Free System Information, Monitoring and Diagnostics\nURL: https://www.hwinfo.com/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: Fred\nHighlights:\nHWiNFO - Free System Information, Monitoring and Diagnostics\n...\n# Professional System Information and Diagnostics\n...\nComprehensive Hardware Analysis, Monitoring and Reporting for Windows and DOS.\n...\n### In-depth Hardware Information\n...\nFrom a quick overview unfolding into the depth of all hardware components. Always up-to date supporting latest technologies and standards.\n...\n### Real-Time System Monitoring\n...\nAccurate monitoring of all system components for actual status and failure prediction. Customizable interface with variety of options. Optimized for lowest overhead.\n...\n### Extensive Reporting\n...\nMultiple types of reports, status logging and interfacing with other tools or add-ons.\n...\n### Trusted and Reliable\n...\nTrusted by thousands of users including large enterprises, main hardware vendors and component manufacturers. Designed to provide most accurate and reliable information.\n...\n### Clean and Secure\n...\nHWiNFO doesn’t collect any personal information and doesn’t transmit any data over network.\n...\n### Frequent Updates\n...\nUpdated frequently to support latest components, technologies and standards. Many systems supported ahead of launch.\n...\n> \"I preferred HWInfo64 due to its stability, data widget, and real-time system monitoring. The competing programs are no slouches, but the free HWInfo64 is a multifaceted champ.\"\n...\nThe Best Free\n...\nBest Free System Information\n\n---\n\nTitle: HWiNFO Download v8.48\nURL: https://www.guru3d.com/download/hwinfo64-download/\nPublished: 2026-05-27T07:08:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n| About this\n...\n| --- |\n...\n| Developer |\n...\nFile Size | 15 MB\n...\n| Date |\n...\n| Operating Systems | WindowsWindows 64bit |\n...\n| License | Freeware\n...\nDownload HWiNFO64 - a System Information and Diagnostics Tool. HWInfo64 is an application that monitors your PC's components and outs computer information about your the operating system, storage capacity, and RAM. It also displays more technical data, such as the number of logical CPUs, memory speed, and temperatures. HWiNFO is a professional hardware information and diagnostic tools supporting latest components, industry technologies, and standards. Both tools are targeted to recognize and extract the most possible amount of information about computer's hardware which makes them suitable for users searching for driver updates, computer manufacturers, system integrators and technical experts too.\n...\nHWiNFO has received another incremental update, continuing its focus on expanding hardware compatibility and refining sensor monitoring across modern platforms. The latest version introduces support for newer components while addressing several accuracy issues related to CPU, GPU, and system telemetry, reinforcing its role as a key utility for system diagnostics.\n...\nAdditional enhancements extend to storage, power, and motherboard monitoring. The update introduces reporting of maximum power for NVMe drives and adds support for Corsair HXi SHIFT power supplies. It also expands compatibility with newer components such as Intel Arc Pro B65 and B70 graphics cards and MPS MP2825 VR PWM controllers. Users can now monitor page file usage more effectively, while DIMM SPD write-protection management adds another layer of control for memory modules.\n...\nLatest v8.46 Released on Apr-14-2026\n...\n- Enhanced sensor monitoring on ASRock X870/X870E Challenger and X870E Taichi OCF.\n...\nmaximum and rated\n...\n50-series GPUs.\n...\n- Fixed monitoring\n...\n6 series.\n...\n- Added Intel Arc Pro B65 and B70.\n...\n- Added support of MPS MP2825 VR PWM.\n...\n- Added reporting of\n...\nFile Total and Used.\n...\n- Added DIMM SPD\n...\nLatest v8.4\n...\nReleased on Mar-04-202\n...\nsupport of Aqua Computer AMPINEL.\n...\n- Fixed Auto Start on some systems using localized Windows.\n...\n- Added sensor values for maximum and rated GPU power limit for NVIDIA GPUs.\n...\noption to disable USB Type-C PD access.\n...\n- Fixed DIMM polling on ASUS TRX50/WRX90 systems with\n...\nHub support. Improved support of\n...\ngeneration AMD CPUs and APUs\n...\nAdded main report and sensor logging in\n...\nmain report and sensor logging in\n...\nboards. Added\n\n---\n\nTitle: HWiNFO Pro Review – Hardware Sensor Monitoring Tool for Personal Users｜PC Monitoring Kawaii – Simple System Monitoring & Network Activity Guides for Global Users\nURL: https://kawaii-pcmonitoring-guide.com/hwinfo-pro-review/\nPublished: 2026-02-24T22:53:03.000Z\nAuthor: admin\nHighlights:\nThe core software is available for free for personal use. The Pro licence extends usage rights to commercial environments and adds a few additional features. This review covers both what makes the free version genuinely capable and where the Pro version adds value.\n...\nHWiNFO is free for personal use with full sensor monitoring and hardware identification features included. HWiNFO Pro extends the licence to cover commercial use, adds portable installation support, removes the reminder to register, and includes a few additional interface options. The distinction between free and Pro is primarily about commercial usage rights rather than a significant feature gap for home users.\n...\nPortable Mode (Pro) The Pro version supports\n...\ndrive without installation\n...\nHWiNFO is free for personal, non-commercial use and includes the full sensor monitoring, hardware identification, logging, and alert features. There is no feature restriction in the free version for home users.\n...\nHWiNFO Pro is available as a paid licence and covers commercial use, adds portable installation support, and removes the periodic registration reminder. For individual home users, the free version is fully functional, and the decision to purchase Pro is primarily relevant for users who need commercial usage rights or portable installation.\n...\n- Among the broadest sensor coverage available, exposing values that many competing tools do not read\n...\n- Full feature set available for free for personal use, with no monitoring or logging restrictions\n...\n- CSV logging captures complete sensor records for post-session analysis\n...\n- Integrates with popular third-party overlay and dashboard tools\n...\n- Active development with regular\n...\n- Initial setup for third-party overlay integration requires configuration in the external tool, not just HWiNFO\n...\n- Pro licence is primarily for commercial use; home users receive the\n...\nPro is well suited for technically experienced Windows users who want the most complete hardware sensor readout available, particularly overclockers, hardware enthusiasts, and reviewers who rely on accurate and detailed data for performance analysis\n...\nfree version covers the full monitoring feature set for personal use, making it a strong choice for home users before considering the Pro upgrade.\n...\nThe free version is fully functional for personal use, which means most home users can access everything the software offers without cost. The Pro licence is most relevant for commercial users and those who need portable installation. For technically engaged Windows users who want accurate, comprehensive hardware data and reliable logging, HWiNFO remains one of the most trusted and consistently maintained tools in this category.\n\n---\n\nTitle: HWiNFO64 7.00 Free and Commercial License - gHacks Tech News\nURL: https://www.ghacks.net/2021/03/09/hwinfo64-7-00-split-into-free-and-commercial-versions/\nPublished: 2021-03-09T14:46:45.000Z\nAuthor: Martin Brinkmann\nHighlights:\nThe Free version is limited to personal, private use, while Commercial/Pro (around £18.06/$29+) adds advanced features like command-line ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: HWiNFO Manual | PDF | Installation (Computer Programs) | Windows Registry\nURL: https://www.scribd.com/document/707547967/HWiNFO-Manual\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThis document is the manual for HWiNFO32/64, a system information and diagnostics tool. It provides an overview of the program, including its system requirements, installation process, feature differences between freeware and pro versions, how to start and configure the program, and descriptions of its main interface elements and sensors monitoring. It aims to help users understand and make full use of HWiNFO's hardware analysis and monitoring capabilities.\n...\nThis document is the manual for HWiNFO32/64, a system information and diagnostics tool. It provides an overview of the program, including its system requirements, installation process, feature differences between freeware and pro versions, how to start and configure the program, and descriptions of its main interface elements and sensors monitoring. It aims to help users understand and make full use of HWiNFO's hardware analysis and monitoring capabilities.\n...\n## 4. Freeware Version vs. Pro Version\n...\nStarting with HWiNFO64 version 7.00, a freeware version and a Pro version isavailable.\n...\n## All versions are free to use in personal and non-commercial environments.\n...\nUsing HWiNFO64 in a commercial environment requires the HWiNFO64 Prolicense. The following table contains the general function matrix:\n...\nAutomatic reportvia command-line\n...\nAutomaticsensor logging\n...\nShared Memorysupport 12-hour limit Unlimited Unlimited (*4)\n...\nRemoteMonitoring (maxmachines) (5) (5 + n) 12-hour limit (*5)\n...\n## 2 - HWiNFO64\n...\n## 3 - HWiNFO64 Pro can be used in commercial environment only with the\n\nEngineer or Corporate License. The Personal license does not allow commercialuse.\n...\n## 4 - HWiNFO64 (non-Pro) has a time-limited Shared Memory support to 12\n...\nhours. When this limit is reached during run-time, this feature will beautomatically deactivated (and requires manual enabling again).\n...\n5 - Each HWiNFO64 Pro license increases the remote connection limit by thenumber of licenses. A Personal license by 5 computers, Corporate and Engineerby 1. For example, 2 Personal licenses will allow 5 + 2*5 = 15 connections.The maximum number of remote connections is currently 50. Remote SensorMonitoring in non-Pro HWiNFO64 is limited to 12 hours as this feature is basedon Shared Memory.\n...\nAny Pro version purchased doesn't expire and remains licensed perpetually.There are different types of maintenance licenses available: Subscription, or aLifetime (Perpetual) license.\n...\n## 5.2. Automatic Update (Pro Version)\n...\ncontinuously evolving IT market. HWiNFO is continuously updated with stablereleases as well as beta releases. While the non-Pro version only notifies aboutnew updates, the HWiNFO64 Pro can perform the whole update automaticallyby one click.",
