      "output": "Title: HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement - iFixit Repair Guide\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/HP+Omen+15-CE0XX+Fan+Replacement/157629\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nHP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement - iFixit Repair Guide\n...\n# HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement\n...\nThis guide will walk you through the process of replacing a faulty ventilation fan in your HP Omen 15-CE0XX laptop. A malfunctioning fan can cause overheating and system instability, leading to potential permanent damage to your device. It is important to take appropriate precautions before beginning the fan replacement process to ensure a successful outcome.\n...\nyour data and review any\n...\nthe root cause of the issue.\n...\nThroughout the process, you will need basic tools such as screwdrivers, prying tools and a replacement fan that is compatible with the HP Omen 15-CE0XX. You should follow the instructions closely and handle the internal components with care to avoid any damage.\n...\nOnce you have completed the fan replacement, it is important to test your\n...\nto ensure that it is\n...\nand without overheating. This guide is intended for individuals with basic technical skills, but if you are unsure or not confident in your abilities, it is always\n...\n## What you need\n...\n## Step 1 Fan\n...\nUse a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the eight 5.5 mm screws from the bottom cover.\n...\nUse a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the two 10 (?) mm screws from the bottom cover.\n...\n## Step 2\n...\nUse a plastic opening tool to gently separate the bottom cover from the main chassis, and pull the cover upwards.\n...\n## Step 3\n...\nUnscrew the four 5.5 mm screws that connect the battery to the main system, and gently detach the battery.\n...\nWhile removing, make sure to avoid pulling the battery straight out. Instead gently lift the lower half of the battery and slide it away from the motherboard in an away and upwards motion.\n...\n## Step 4\n...\nRemove the trunk outlet for the replacement fan. This is done by unscrewing the three 5.5mm screws on the trunk outlet and then sliding it outwards to remove.\n...\n## Step 5\n...\nUse a Phillips #00 screwdriver to unscrew the five 5.5 mm screws that secure the bracket to the frame.\n...\nAfter all screws are loose, gently lift the bracket upwards.\n...\nBe careful with the power cable sitting right under this bracket. You might have to move the cable around gently to get the bracket out\n...\n## Step 6\n...\nDisconnect the fan cable from the motherboard using a plastic opening/ pry tool.\n...\nDo not use too much force while pulling the fan cable as it may break. If required, you may use a secondary plastic opening/pry tool for support.\n...\n## Step 7\n...\nCarefully pull the fan out, clean the dust if required.\n...\nFinally, you can now replace the faulty fan with the new fan by following the above steps in reverse order.\n...\nTo reassemble your device, follow these instructions in reverse order.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Hewlett-Packard (HP) Omen 15-CE0XX Notebook Parts | Impact Computers\nURL: https://impactcomputers.com/index.php/collections/hewlett-packard-hp-omen-15-ce0xx-notebook-parts\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nHewlett-Packard (HP) Omen 15-CE0XX Notebook Parts | Impact Computers\n...\n# Select the family or model of Hewlett-Packard (HP) Omen 15-CE0XX Notebook Parts equipment (Hewlett-Packard (HP) Omen 15-CE0XX Notebook Parts)\n...\nBatteries (4)\n...\nCooling Fans/ Heatsinks (3)\n...\nMemory (1)\n...\n752920-019 - 15.6 INCH FHD UWVA 220 eDP Slim PRT LCD Panel\n...\n: Hewlett-packard (HP)\n...\n766644-001 - 1.0tb Sata Hard Disk Drive\n...\nBrand: Hewlett-packard (HP)\n...\n862398-850 - Sodimm 8GB 2400mhz 1.2V Memory Module\n...\nBrand: Hewlett-packard (HP)\n...\n929455-001 - Fan, Left (DTA47G3ATP003)\n...\n929456-001 - FAN, Right - With Thermal pad From Supplier\n...\n92944\n...\n-001 -\n...\nENNA,\n...\n-packard\n...\n917724-855 - 15.4v Batt 4C 70WH 4.55ah LI Battery (SR04070XL-PL)\n...\nBrand: Hewlett\n...\npackard (HP)\n...\nHewlett-packard\n...\n929561-001 - BRACKET, HDD Left and Right\n...\n: Hewlett-packard\n...\n: Hewlett-packard\n...\nHewlett-packard\n...\nHewlett-packard\n...\n929450-001 - CABLE, HDD\n...\nHewlett-packard\n...\n929448-001 - Cable, Power Board\n...\nHewlett-packard\n...\n: Hewlett-packard\n\n---\n\nTitle: OMEN by HP 15 ce000, dc0000 PCs - Replace the battery\nURL: https://support.hp.com/gb-en/document/ish_2518413-1409566-16\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nOMEN by HP 15 ce000, dc0000 PCs - Replace the battery | HP® Support\n...\nAll](#)\n...\n# OMEN by HP 15 ce000, dc0000 PCs - Replace the battery\n...\nIf the battery crashes, is damaged, or needs upgrading, you can replace the battery.\n...\nThis product contains components that can be damaged by electrostatic discharge (ESD). HP recommends using an anti-static\nwrist strap and working over a non-carpeted floor with a conductive foam pad to reduce the to reduce the chance of electrostatic\ndischarge (ESD) damage.\n...\n## Prepare for replacing parts of the computer\n...\n1. Turn\n...\nwait for components to cool.\n...\n2. Disconnect the power cord and any cables from the computer, and then unplug the power cord from the wall outlet, surge protector,\n...\nextension cable, or power strip.\n...\n3. Transfer the computer to a clear, flat, stable work surface over a non-carpeted floor with a conductive foam pad to reduce\nthe chance of electrostatic discharge (ESD) damage. HP recommends using anti-static wrist straps.\n...\n4. Keep and parts or components in their protective packaging until you are ready to install them.\n...\n5. Make sure you have a Phillips or Flathead screwdriver, depending on your computer model.\n...\n## Remove the battery\n...\nRemove the battery from inside the computer.\n...\n1. Remove the top cover.\n...\n![Removing the top cover\n...\n2. Use a Phillips-head screwdriver to remove the four 5mm (0.19 in) screws that secure the battery in place.\n...\nthe battery, and\n...\nthe base enclosure to\n...\nthe battery.\n...\n## Replace the battery\n...\nReplace the battery, and then secure it in place inside the computer.\n...\n1. Using both hands, slide the front edge of the battery into the cut-outs, and then lower the rear edge onto its connector on\nthe system board.\n...\n![Replacing the battery](https://kaas.hpcloud.hp.com/PROD/v2/renderbinary/2818764/1409425/con-omen-p-omen15ce000-omen15dc0000-replace-battery/nb-omen-15ce000-replace-battery)\n...\n2. Use a Phillips-head screwdriver to replace the four 5mm (0.19 in) screws that secure the battery in place.\n...\n![Locating the screws to remove them](https://kaas.hpcloud.hp.com/PROD/v2/renderbinary/2818764/1409283/con-omen-p-omen15ce000-omen15dc0000-replace-battery/nb-omen-15ce000-remove-screws)\n...\n3. Replace the top cover.\n...\n![Replacing the top cover](https://kaas.hpcloud.hp.com/PROD/v2/renderbinary/2818764/1409409/con-omen-p-omen15ce000-omen15dc0000-replace-battery/nb-omen-15ce000-replace-top-cover)\n\n---\n\nTitle: Solved: Upgrade SSD and RAM HP OMEN 15-ce0xx - HP Support Community - 7695327\nURL: https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Gaming-Notebooks/Upgrade-SSD-and-RAM-HP-OMEN-15-ce0xx/td-p/7695327\nPublished: 2020-07-20T18:38:31.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nSolved: Upgrade SSD and RAM HP OMEN 15-ce0xx - HP Support Community - 7695327\n...\nProduct: OMEN by HP Laptop 15-ce0xx\n...\nI have an OMEN HP Laptop 15-ce0xx\n...\nGX62\n...\n#ABM\n...\nI would like to upgrade my laptop. I am thinking about getting more RAM and replacing the mechanical HDD to start.\n...\n1. Is it possible to add (or change out) the RAM? - If so, which model should I look at to upgrade?\n2. Can I replace the HDD 7200rpm with an SSD? - if so, what's the best model out there?\n...\nYour machine is an OMEN by HP - 15-ce002la, its specs\n...\n1. RAM: It has 12 GB de SDRAM DDR4-2133 (1 x 4 GB, 1 x 8 GB) now and supports 16GB max. You can replace 4GB with same existing 8GB or use the following compatible RAM\n...\nhttps://www.crucial.com/memory/ddr4/ct8g4sfs824a/ct10886643(RAM will run at 2133MHz).\n...\n2. STORAGE: You have 2 options\n...\n(a) Replace 1TB HDD with 1TB 2.5\" SATA SSD using\n...\nhttps://www.crucial.com/products/ssd/crucial-mx500-ssd https://www.samsung.com/semiconductor/minisite/ssd/product/consumer/860evo/ Or similar from reputable vendors. One example\n...\n(b) Add M.2 NVMe SSD (highly recommended) using\n...\nhttps://www.samsung.com/au/memory-storage/970-evo-nvme-m2-ssd/MZ-V7E2T0BW/ https://www.crucial.com/products/ssd/crucial-p2-ssd https://www.crucial.com/products/ssd/crucial-p5-ssd Or similar from reputable vendors. One example\n...\nLaptop 1\n...\nYour machine is an OMEN by HP - 15-ce002la, its specs\n...\n1. RAM: It has 12 GB de SDRAM DDR4-2133 (1 x 4 GB, 1 x 8 GB) now and supports 16GB max. You can replace 4GB with same existing 8GB or use the following compatible RAM\n...\nhttps://www.crucial.com/memory/ddr4/ct8g4sfs824a/ct10886643(RAM will run at 2133MHz).\n...\n2. STORAGE: You have 2 options\n...\n(a) Replace 1TB HDD with 1TB 2.5\" SATA SSD using\n...\nhttps://www.crucial.com/products/ssd/crucial-mx500-ssd https://www.samsung.com/semiconductor/minisite/ssd/product/consumer/860evo/ Or similar from reputable vendors. One example\n...\n(b) Add M.2 NVMe SSD (highly recommended) using\n...\nhttps://www.samsung.com/au/memory-storage/970-evo-nvme-m2-ssd/MZ-V7E2T0BW/ https://www.crucial.com/products/ssd/crucial-p2-ssd https://www.crucial.com/products/ssd/crucial-p5-ssd Or similar from reputable vendors. One example\n...\nMZ-V7E2T0 | MZ\n...\nV7E2\n...\nOMEN by HP Laptop 15-ce0xx\n\n---\n\nTitle: HP OMEN MAINTENANCE AND SERVICE MANUAL Pdf Download | ManualsLib\nURL: https://www.manualslib.com/manual/1308336/Hp-Omen.html\nPublished: 2017-10-17T05:55:10.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n### Page 43: Battery\n...\n### Page 62: Fans\n...\nComponent Description Vents Enable airflow to cool internal compone