    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"# Contributing to WHEA Diagnostic Toolkit\\n\\nThank you for your interest in contributing! This project is especially welcoming to:\\n\\n- **Students** who've fixed their own laptops using these tools\\n- **IT support teams** with enterprise deployment experience\\n- **Developers** who want to add Linux/macOS support\\n\\n## How to Contribute\\n\\n### 1. Report Issues\\n\\nIf you encounter a bug or have a suggestion:\\n\\n1. Check existing [issues](https://github.com/andiekobbie/whea-diagnostic-toolkit/issues)\\n2. If not found, create a new issue with:\\n   - Your system specs (CPU, RAM, GPU, OS version)\\n   - The exact error message or unexpected behavior\\n   - Steps to reproduce\\n\\n### 2. Submit Code Changes\\n\\n1. Fork the repository\\n2. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feature/your-feature`\\n3. Make your changes\\n4. Test on at least one Windows 10/11 system\\n5. Commit with clear message: `git commit -m \\\"Add: description of change\\\"`\\n6. Push and create a Pull Request\\n\\n### 3. Add Hardware Compatibility\\n\\nTested a new laptop model? Add it to the compatibility list:\\n\\n```markdown\\n### Tested Hardware\\n\\n- HP OMEN 15-ce0xx (primary development platform)\\n- Dell XPS 15 9570\\n- [YOUR MODEL] (tested by [your name])\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Improve Documentation\\n\\n- Fix typos or unclear explanations\\n- Add translations\\n- Create video tutorials\\n- Write blog posts about your experience\\n\\n## Development Guidelines\\n\\n### PowerShell Scripts\\n\\n- Use `#Requires -Version 5.1` for compatibility\\n- Avoid external module dependencies\\n- Test with `-WhatIf` parameter where applicable\\n- Include proper error handling with `try/catch`\\n\\n### Python Scripts\\n\\n- Maintain compatibility with Python 3.8+\\n- Use `psutil` for cross-platform compatibility\\n- Keep external dependencies minimal\\n- Include docstrings for all functions\\n\\n### Documentation\\n\\n- Use clear, non-technical language where possible\\n- Include examples for common use cases\\n- Test all code snippets before committing\\n\\n## Code of Conduct\\n\\n- Be respectful and inclusive\\n- Help newcomers learn\\n- Focus on practical solutions\\n- Share knowledge freely\\n\\n## Questions?\\n\\nOpen an issue or reach out to [@andiekobbie](https://github.com/andiekobbie).\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Note:** This project is particularly interested in contributions that help **students and sixth-formers** diagnose and fix their laptops without expensive repair visits.\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\Documents\\\\whea-diagnostic-toolkit\\\\CONTRIBUTING.md\"}",
