      "output": "Title: Job Openings\nURL: https://ifixit.breezy.hr/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nCome work with us! View Openings. iFixit is a small company with a big goal: we want to show the world how to fix everything. iFixit is a great place to work.\n\n---\n\nTitle: iFixit Careers | Join Our Mission to Repair the World!\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/about-us/careers/jobs-de\nPublished: 2026-06-17T17:09:59.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\niFixit is a hybrid company, which means that all steps of our application process can take place remotely. Unless you are applying for a job in our Operations ...\n\n---\n\nTitle: Jobs at iFixit USA San Luis Obispo, CA and Chattanooga, TN\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/about-us/careers/jobs-usa\nPublished: 2026-06-11T21:31:33.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nAs part of iFixit, you have the opportunity to work on innovative projects and promote cultural awareness around repair.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Career Page Home - iFixit\nURL: https://www.ifixit.com/about-us/careers\nPublished: 2026-06-26T10:18:33.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nA career that makes a real difference. iFixit is the online platform with free repair guides for every thing, written by everyone.\n\n---\n\nTitle: iFixit Jobs & Careers - Remote, Work From Home & Flexible - FlexJobs\nURL: https://www.flexjobs.com/remote-jobs/company/ifixit\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nFind remote work from home jobs and careers with iFixit. Get a better remote job search with FlexJobs today!\n\n---\n\nTitle: Firmware Engineer - iFixit | Built In\nURL: https://builtin.com/job/firmware-engineer/2273166\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nFirmware Engineer - iFixit | Built In\n...\n## iFixit\n...\n# Firmware Engineer\n...\nSorry, this job was removed at 05:17 p.m. (UTC) on Monday, Feb 24, 2025\n...\nHiring Remotely in Chattanooga, TN, USA\n...\nIn-Office or Remote\n...\nWe're looking for a talented and creative person to help iFixit deliver excellent repair experiences. As a Firmware design engineer, you'll be working alongside the rest of the product development team to design and implement the next generation of repair tools. You should be comfortable working with Linux, schematics, and lab equipment such as an oscilloscope.\n...\n- Be a key Firmware contributor in iFixit's innovation-driven NPI process.\n...\n- Develop and optimize firmware for our upcoming products, ensuring\n...\nand reliable operation of embedded systems.\n...\nto define firmware\n...\n, and integration\n...\n- Debug and\n...\niFixit is a great place to work, here are some of our perks:\n...\n- 401k plan with 4% employer match.\n- Full benefits package. Competitive medical, dental, vision and life insurance with generous employer contribution. Plus a stipend toward coverage for your dependent(s).\n- Dependent Care FSA.\n- Company paid short term disability.\n- Flexible vacation time, paid holidays, and volunteer time off.\n- Generous stipends towards repair & wellness.\n- $400 towards a bike or alternative method of transportation.\n- $100 towards a pair of headphones.\n- Employee discounts on parts and tools.\n- Charitable contribution matching: we'll 100% match your tax deductible donations.\n...\nTo Apply:\n...\nUpload a .pdf of your resume and a short cover letter. Be sure to tell us about your design experience, and include some screenshots or renders of examples of your work, if you’re able.\n...\nView all jobs at iFixit\n...\nView all jobs at iFixit\n...\niFixit\n\n---\n\nTitle: PR Coordinator at iFixit\nURL: https://ifixit.breezy.hr/p/b9f2903fc54f-pr-coordinator\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nPR Coordinator at iFixit\n...\nTo accomplish those goals, we’re looking for a Public Relations Coordinator to join our marketing and editorial teams.\n...\n### You must:\n...\n- Consume a lot of information and react quickly to keep up with the fast-moving pace of digital media\n- Have the ability to conceptualize highly technical concepts and the iFixit brand (and translate them to less technical and unfamiliar audiences)\n- Have a degree in Journalism or 3+ years in equivalent experience in public relations or news media\n\n- Organization and attention to detail\n- Exceptional grammar and\n...\n### iFixit is an awesome place to work. Here are some of our perks:\n...\n- Charitable contribution matching! We'll 100% match your contribution, tax deductible.\n- Employee discounts on parts and tools.\n- A sweet pair of headphones to get your head in the game.\n- $400 towards a bike or alternative method of transportation.\n- Generous stipends towards repair & wellness.\n- Company paid short term disability.\n- Full benefits package. Competitive medical, dental, vision and life insurance with generous employer contribution. Plus a stipend toward coverage for your dependent(s).\n- 401k plan with 4% employer match.\n- Work laptop, and any software you need.\n...\n### iFixit’s Expansion to Chattanooga\n...\nWe are excited to have moved into our eastern distribution hub and headquarters! We've built a 50,000 square foot flagship location blocks from downtown in\n...\nhistoric Onion Bottom\n...\non 12th\n...\n### When applying:\n...\nAttach a PDF resume and a PDF cover letter explaining two things:\n...\n1. Why you're the ideal candidate for this job.\n2. Why you're badass, and\n...\nInclude links to your portfolio, public social media accounts (if you have them), and create a pitch based on “appliance repair” to showcase your PR skills.\n\n---\n\nTitle: Wholesale Operations Specialist\nURL: https://builtin.com/job/wholesale-operations-specialist/3221793\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nJobs](https://\n...\n.com/\n...\n[For Employers](https://employers.builtin.com/membership?utm_medium=BIReferral&utm_source=foremployers)\n...\n[Join](https://builtin.com/auth/signup?destination=/job/wholesale-operations-specialist/3221793)\n...\n[Log In](https://builtin.com/auth/login?destination=/job/wholesale-operations-specialist/3221793)\n...\n[![https://cdn.builtin.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,fit=scale-down,w=200,h=200/https://builtin.com/sites/www.builtin.com/files/2022-09/1_269.jpg Logo](https://cdn.builtin.com/cdn-cgi/image/f=auto,fit=scale-down,w=200,h=200/https://builtin.com/sites/www.builtin.com/files/2022-09/1_269.jpg)](https://builtin.com/company/ifixit)[## iFixit\n...\n](https://builtin.com/company/ifixit)\n# Wholesale Operations Specialist\n**Sorry, this job was removed at 06:33 p.m. (CST) on Sunday, Feb 09, 2025\n**\nHiring Remotely inChattanooga, TN\n**\nRemote\nSoftware\n...\n**iFixit’s Expansion to Chattanooga:**Our roots are in the California technology startup world, but our passion is tinkering. We are thrilled to be joining the making and manufacturing culture of Tennessee.\n...\nhistoric Onion Bottom neighborhood on 12th street.\n...\n**\n**iFixit is an awesome place to work.****Here are some of our perks:**\n* A career where you will be actively working to make the world better.\n* A repairable laptop, and any software you need.\n* Full benefits package. Employer-paid health insurance through Anthem Blue Cross including medical, dental, vision, and life insurance. Plus a stipend toward coverage for your dependent(s).\n* 401k plan with 4% employer match.\n* Flexible vacation time + paid holidays.\n* Dependent Care FSA.\n* Generous stipends towards repair &amp; wellness.\n* $400 towards a bike or alternative method of transportation.\n* A sweet pair of headphones to get your head in the game.\n* Team member discounts on parts and tools.\n* Charitable contribution matching! We'll 100% match your tax deductible contribution.\n...\n[**View all jobs at iFixit](https://builtin.com/company/ifixit/jobs)\n[**View iFixit Profile](https://builtin.com/company/ifixit)\n**Report Job\n...\nThe Company\n**\nHQ: San Luis Obispo, CA\n**\n166 Employees\n**\nOn-site Workplace\n**\nYear Founded: 2003\n...\n## What We Do\n...\n[**View all jobs at iFixit](https://builtin.com/company/ifixit/jobs)\n[**View iFixit Profile](https://builtin.com/company/ifixit)\n**Report Job\nContinue\n...\n[Log In to apply](https://builtin.com/auth/login?destination=/job/wholesale-operations-specialist/3221793)[Sign up to apply](https://builtin.com/auth/signup?destination=/job/wholesale-operations-specialist/3221793)\nApply Instructions\n...\nagree to[\n...\n](https://builtin.com/jobs/remote)",
